This is a plain reference document, not source code — the leaf format still applies but the content is simple to describe.

`docs/STATUS.md` is a human-curated project priority backlog: a single markdown table of outstanding work items, each tagged with impact/difficulty and provenance (`*(audit 2026-07-18)*` vs `*(prior audit)*`), sorted by impact descending then difficulty ascending within band. It is generated/maintained by hand, not derived from `ctx-context`, and is explicitly excluded from the auto-generated context tree (its own header says architecture docs are derived elsewhere; this file is the task list, not architecture).

Key facts an editor needs: entries reference specific file:line locations in the actual codebase (e.g. `checks.rs:211`, `hook.rs`) that will drift if those files change — this doc is not re-verified automatically, so stale line numbers are expected and not a bug to "fix" without checking the current source. The `docs/retired/AUDIT.md` is the historical predecessor; its blanket "resolve remaining findings" task was superseded by explicit line items here, and only the still-valid remainder was carried forward (marked `*(prior audit)*`). One known finding (`.context` orphan-reconciliation) is deliberately omitted because it's already being worked by a separate agent — don't re-add it without checking whether that work landed.

When editing: preserve the sort order (impact desc, then difficulty asc within impact), keep the audit-provenance tags, and update "Last updated" date at the top when the table changes.